{"title_page": "James Sears", "text_new": "{{Infobox criminal \n| name          = James Sears\n| image         = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Dimitrious Sarafopoulos\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1963|9|14}}\n| birth_place   = \n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| other_names   = \"Dimitri the Lover\"\n| occupation    = physician (license revoked)\n| conviction_status  =Convicted January 24, 2019, sentenced August 22, 2019. Released on bail pending appeal\n| apprehended        = \n| imprisoned         =\n| image_name         = \n| conviction           = 2 counts of [[hate speech laws in Canada|willful promotion of hate]]\n| conviction_penalty = 1 year imprisonment (6 months each count, served consecutively)\n}}\n'''James Nicholas Sears''' (born '''Dimitrious Sarafopoulos''';<ref name=\"ncparty\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ncparty.ca/leader.html |title=Message From NCP Leader, Dr. James Sears |publisher=New Constitution Party of Canada |accessdate=October 26, 2015}}</ref> September 14, 1963)<ref>https://twitter.com/dimitrithelover</ref><ref name=guru/> is a Canadian [[perennial candidate]], and a professional [[pickup artist]] under the pseudonym '''Dimitri the Lover'''. He was the editor of an [[antisemitic]] tabloid promoting his own [[New Constitution Party]]. The newspaper, titled ''Your Ward News'', was barred from distribution by [[Canada Post]] in 2016, and Sears was convicted of [[hate speech laws in Canada|willful promotion of hate]] in 2019. On the day of the ruling, Twitter suspended his account ''@dimitrithelover''. On August 22, 2019 he was sentenced to imprisonment for one year.<ref name=jail>https://www.theglobeandmail.com/amp/canada/toronto/article-your-ward-news-editor-james-sears-sentenced-to-one-year-in-jail-for/</ref> On August 27, 2019, Sears was released on bail pending the hearing of his appeal.<ref name=bail/>\n\n==Medical and military background==\nSears was trained as a [[physician]] and described himself as a retired Canadian Armed Forces Medical Officer ([[Captain (Canadian army and air force)|Captain]]).<ref>[https://www.canlii.org/en/on/oncpsd/doc/1993/1993oncpsd9/1993oncpsd9.html Quoted in ''The College of Surgeons and Physicians of Ontario vs. Dr. James Sears''], December 1, 1992 - \"'If Captain Sears returns to medical practice, he should be supervised carefully.'\" (1990)</ref><ref name=\"ncparty\" /> In the 1980s while a medical student with the Canadian Armed Forces, Sears was noted for erratic behaviour, and graduated in 1988, despite \"documented reservations\". During his subsequent internship, he was judged \"immature\" and entered psychotherapy in 1990. Following complaints from female patients, Sears' medical licence was revoked by the [[College of Physicians and Surgeons of Ontario]] in 1992 after Sears pleaded guilty to two counts of sexual assault.<ref name=guru>{{cite news|title=Disgraced doctor is T.O.'s seduction guru|url=http://www.torontosun.com/news/torontoandgta/2008/12/31/7891486.html|accessdate=May 20, 2015|work=Toronto Sun|date=December 30, 2008|quote=\"By 1986, Sears was in the Canadian Armed Forces and while still a third-year medical student was evaluated by a military psychiatrist who suggested there was \"something seriously wrong\" with Sears.\"}}</ref>\n\nSears started the Second Opinion Medical-Legal Consultants Group in 1994, offering \"medical investigative services\" such as medical background checks for the prospective employees of its clients and research for parties to medical malpractice suits. In 2001, it was reported in the ''Toronto Star'' that they had been hired by Canadian Tire and the Toronto Transit Commission.<ref name=torontoist>{{Cite web | url=http://torontoist.com/2017/04/controversial-publisher-ward-news-send-homophobic-hate-mail-councillor-wong-tam/ |title = Did the Controversial Editor of Your Ward News Send Homophobic Hate Mail to Councillor Wong-Tam?|date = 2017-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Mortgage broker==\nHe has also been involved with the [[mortgage brokerage]] industry with Trillium Mortgages and then Expert Mortgage Company. His application for a mortgage broker's licence was denied by the regulatory body, the [[Financial Services Commission of Ontario]]; however, he has continued to work for Expert Mortgage Company as a \"full-time in-house marketing guru\", describing himself as \"Ontario\u2019s #1 Trainer of Sales Consultants, with Specialization in Mortgage & Real Estate Agents.\"<ref name=torontoist/>\n\n==Pickup artist==\nSears was also known for his activities as a [[pickup artist]] using the pseudonym \"Dimitri the Lover\" selling courses that claimed to train men in how to seduce women.<ref name=torontoist/>\n\n==Politics==\nIn the [[2014 Toronto municipal election|2014 Toronto civic election]], Sears was a [[Toronto City Council|city council]] candidate in Ward 32 and received 797 votes (roughly 3% of the vote).<ref name=\"toronto\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.toronto.ca/City%20Of%20Toronto/City%20Clerks/Elections/Library/Files/Results%20PDFs/2014%20Election/2014-Councillor.pdf|date=31 October 2014|title=2014 Municipal Election Results - Councillor Poll by Poll|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Dimitri the Lover' back making headlines|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2015/03/25/dimitri-the-lover-back-making-headlines|accessdate=May 20, 2015|work=Toronto Sun|date=March 25, 2015}}</ref> His campaign included a website with an interactive animation that asked users to choose one of three playable characters, [[Rob Ford]], [[Vladimir Putin]] or [[Adolf Hitler]] to \"spank\" the bare bottom of a cartoon caricature of city councillor [[Mary-Margaret McMahon]], Sears's rival in the election.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toronto city council candidate James Sears promotes online 'spanking' game against female rival|url=http://o.canada.com/news/james-sears-animation-mcmahon-492553|accessdate=May 20, 2015|website=canada.com|agency=Postmedia News|date=June 30, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe ran in the [[2015 Canadian federal election|2015 federal election]] as an independent candidate (no party affiliation) and placed fifth out of seven candidates, getting 254 votes (less than 0.5% of the vote).<ref name=\"globalnews\">{{cite web|url=http://globalnews.ca/news/2159630/federal-election-2015-beaches-east-york-riding/|title=Federal Election 2015: Beaches-East York riding results - Toronto &#124; Globalnews.ca|publisher=globalnews.ca|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSears was a candidate for the [[Canadians' Choice Party]] in the [[2018 Ontario general election|2018 provincial election]] running against [[Attorney-General of Ontario|Attorney-General]] [[Yasir Naqvi]] in [[Ottawa Centre (provincial electoral district)|Ottawa Centre]]. He placed last out of eight candidates with 92 votes.<ref>https://www.elections.on.ca/content/ngw/en/election-results/ottawa-centre.html</ref>\n\nIn 2018 he registered as a candidate for [[Mayor of Toronto]] in [[2018 Toronto mayoral election|that year's election]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Editor's message |website=Your Ward News |first=James |last=Sears |date=Winter 2018}}</ref> He finished with 680 votes, less than 1% of the total vote.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.toronto.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/97da-2018clerksofficialdeclarationofresults.pdf| title=2018 Clerks Official Declaration of Results| first=Uli| last=Watkiss| date=October 25, 2018| website=toronto.ca| page=1}}</ref>\n\n==''Your Ward News''==\nSears is editor-in-chief of ''Your Ward News'', a quarterly newspaper which promotes the [[Neo-Nazism in Canada#New Constitution Party of Canada|New Constitution Party]], an unregistered [[Neo-Nazism in Canada|neo-Nazi]] political party led by Sears.<ref name=\"ncparty\" /><ref name=ward/> The newspaper used to be printed and distributed as a [[Flyer (pamphlet)|flyer]] in the east [[Toronto]] neighbourhood of [[The Beaches]]. The [[vanity publication]], which claimed to have a circulation of 50,000,<!-- do not change this figure, see talk page --> was criticized for using [[antisemitic]] caricatures and language, described by former [[Canadian Jewish Congress]] Chief Executive Officer [[Bernie Farber]] as \"classic anti-Semitic tropes\" and \"a clear attempt at a hateful representation of Jews\".<ref name=ward>{{cite news|title=Beach residents decry 'offensive' newsletter|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2015/05/16/beach-residents-decry-offensive-newsletter.html|accessdate=May 20, 2015|work=Toronto Star}}</ref> On June 6, 2016, the [[Government of Canada]] ordered [[Canada Post]] to cease delivery of the paper.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/canada-post-ordered-to-stop-delivering-controversial-your-ward-news-1.3619554 |title=Canada Post ordered to stop delivering controversial Your Ward News |newspaper=CBC News |first=Emmett |last=Shane |date=June 6, 2016 |accessdate=June 7, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe newspaper continued to be distributed using private delivery services, and was investigated for [[hate crime]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/toronto-police-investigating-controversial-your-ward-news-publication-1.3957831 |title=Toronto police investigating controversial Your Ward News publication |newspaper=CBC News |first=Lauren |last=Pelley |date=January 30, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref> On June 21, 2017, Sears and publisher Leroy St. Germaine were charged under the [[Criminal Code (Canada)|Criminal Code]] with uttering threats against [[Warren Kinsella|Warren and Lisa Kinsella]] in an article by Sears in which he wrote that his supporters may decide to \"bludgeon the Kinsellas to death.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citynews.ca/2017/06/21/editor-publisher-of-neo-nazi-tabloid-charged-with-uttering-threats/ |title=Editor, publisher of neo-Nazi tabloid charged with uttering threats |website=CityNews |date=June 21, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://toronto.ctvnews.ca/criminal-charges-laid-against-publisher-of-controversial-newspaper-your-ward-news-1.3470015 |title=Criminal charges laid against publisher of controversial newspaper ''Your Ward News'' |website=CTV News |first=Paola |last=Loriggio |publisher=Canadian Press |date=June 21, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017, Sears and St. Germaine were each charged with two counts of wilful promotion of hatred under the Criminal Code.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/document/398156562/Court-Ruling-Sears-and-St-Germaine|title=Court Ruling - Sears and St. Germaine|website=Scribd|language=en|access-date=2019-01-26}}</ref> They were accused of promoting hatred against women and Jews.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/mobile/canada/2-men-behind-controversial-toronto-publication-face-hate-related-charges-1.3681157 |title=2 men behind controversial Toronto publication face hate-related charges |first=Peter |last=Cameron |publisher=Canadian Press |website=CTV News |date=November 16, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref> Both were found guilty on January 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Your Ward News duo found guilty of peddling hate against women and Jews |first=Colin |last=Perkel |newspaper=CBC News |date=January 24, 2019 |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/your-ward-promoting-hate-1.4990806 |accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref> The Crown asked that Sears be given one-year jail sentence and an additional three-years [[probation]] during which Sears would be prohibited from publishing any material.<ref name=\"year\"/> On August 22, 2019, Sears was sentenced to one year's imprisonment, consisting of six months for each charge, served consecutively, the maximum sentence available.<ref name=jail/><ref name=\"year\">{{cite news |last1=Perkel |first1=Colin |title=Editor found guilty of peddling hate says Your Ward News gave 'angry men' a voice |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/crown-seeks-one-year-jail-term-against-editor-convicted-of-promoting-hate |accessdate=April 27, 2019 |work=National Post |agency=Canadian Press |date=April 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Perkel |first1=Colin |title=James Sears fires lawyer; sentencing for Your Ward News delayed |url=https://www.680news.com/2019/05/30/james-sears-fires-lawyer-sentencing-for-your-ward-news-delayed/ |accessdate=June 22, 2019 |work=680 News |agency=Canadian Press |date=May 30, 2019}}</ref> He is currently out on bail, pending appeal.<ref name=bail>{{Cite web | url=https://toronto.citynews.ca/2019/08/29/germaine-your-ward-news-sentence/ | title=Your Ward News publisher sentenced to 12-month house arrest}}</ref> On August 29, 2019, St. Germaine was sentenced to one year of [[house arrest]].<ref name=bail/>\n\n==Electoral record==\n{| cellpadding=\"8\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|+ '''[[2014 Toronto municipal election|2014 Toronto election]], Ward 32'''<ref name=\"2014muni\">{{cite web |title=Toronto Election 2014 Poll By Poll Results: Councillor |url=https://www.toronto.ca/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/9021-election-2014-councillor-poll-by-poll-results.pdf |publisher=Toronto City Clerk's Office |accessdate=June 11, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ddf; width:250px;\"| Candidate\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ddf;\"| Votes\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ddf;\"| %\n|-\n|[[Mary-Margaret McMahon]]||align=right| 15,762 ||align=right| 60.92\n|-\n|[[Sandra Bussin]] ||align=right| 4,552 ||align=right| 17.59\n|-\n|Brian Graff ||align=right| 1,922 ||align=right| 7.43\n|-\n|'''James Sears''' ||align=right| 797 ||align=right| 3.08\n|-\n|Eric de Boer ||align=right| 677 ||align=right| 2.62\n|-\n|Carmel Suttor ||align=right| 464 ||align=right| 1.79\n|-\n|Alan Burke ||align=right| 404 ||align=right| 1.56\n|-\n|Maria Garcia ||align=right| 402 ||align=right| 1.55\n|-\n|Michael Connor ||align=right| 334 ||align=right| 1.29\n|-\n|Sean Dawson ||align=right| 241 ||align=right| 0.93\n|-\n|Bruce Baker ||align=right| 213 ||align=right| 0.82\n|-\n|Jim Brookman ||align=right| 107 ||align=right| 0.41\n|-\n!Total||align=right| 25,875 ||align=right|  100%\n|}\n{{Canadian federal election, 2015/Beaches\u2014East York}}\n{{Ontario provincial election, 2018/Ottawa Centre}}\n\n==Sources==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* [http://ncparty.ca Website of the New Constitution Party]\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sears, James}}\n[[Category:Canadian neo-Nazis]]\n[[Category:Canadian anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Pickup artists]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Greek descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian newspaper editors]]\n[[Category:Canadian male journalists]]\n[[Category:Russian people of Greek descent]]\n[[Category:Pontic Greeks]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Russian descent]]\n[[Category:Eastern Orthodox Christians from Canada]]\n[[Category:1963 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Independent candidates in the 2015 Canadian federal election]]\n[[Category:21st-century Canadian criminals]]\n[[Category:Canadian politicians convicted of crimes]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox criminal \n| name          = James Sears\n| image         = <!-- just the filename, without the File: or Image: prefix or enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = \n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Dimitrious Sarafopoulos\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|1963|9|14}}\n| birth_place   = \n| death_date    = \n| death_place   = \n| nationality   = [[Canadians|Canadian]]\n| other_names   = \"Dimitri the Lover\"\n| occupation    = physician (license revoked)\n| conviction_status  =Convicted January 24, 2019, sentenced August 22, 2019. Released on bail pending appeal\n| apprehended        = \n| imprisoned         =\n| image_name         = \n| conviction           = 2 counts of [[hate speech laws in Canada|willful promotion of hate]]\n| conviction_penalty = 1 year imprisonment (6 months each count, served consecutively)\n}}\n'''James Nicholas Sears''' (born '''Dimitrious Sarafopoulos''';<ref name=\"ncparty\">{{cite web |url=http://www.ncparty.ca/leader.html |title=Message From NCP Leader, Dr. James Sears |publisher=New Constitution Party of Canada |accessdate=October 26, 2015}}</ref> September 14, 1963)<ref>https://twitter.com/dimitrithelover</ref><ref name=guru/> is a Canadian [[perennial candidate]], and a professional [[pickup artist]] under the pseudonym '''Dimitri the Lover'''. He was the editor of an [[antisemitic]] tabloid promoting his own [[New Constitution Party]]. The newspaper, titled ''Your Ward News'', was barred from distribution by [[Canada Post]] in 2016, and Sears was convicted of [[hate speech laws in Canada|willful promotion of hate]] in 2019. On the day of the ruling, Twitter suspended his account ''@dimitrithelover''. On August 22, 2019 he was sentenced to imprisonment for one year.<ref name=jail>https://www.theglobeandmail.com/amp/canada/toronto/article-your-ward-news-editor-james-sears-sentenced-to-one-year-in-jail-for/</ref> On August 27, 2019, Sears was released on bail pending the hearing of his appeal.<ref name=bail/>\n\n==Medical and military background==\nSears was trained as a [[physician]] and described himself as a retired Canadian Armed Forces Medical Officer ([[Captain (Canadian army and air force)|Captain]]).<ref>[https://www.canlii.org/en/on/oncpsd/doc/1993/1993oncpsd9/1993oncpsd9.html Quoted in ''The College of Surgeons and Physicians of Ontario vs. Dr. James Sears''], December 1, 1992 - \"'If Captain Sears returns to medical practice, he should be supervised carefully.'\" (1990)</ref><ref name=\"ncparty\" /> In the 1980s while a medical student with the Canadian Armed Forces, Sears was noted for erratic behaviour, and graduated in 1988, despite \"documented reservations\". During his subsequent internship, he was judged \"immature\" and entered psychotherapy in 1990. Following complaints from female patients, Sears' medical licence was revoked by the [[College of Physicians and Surgeons of Ontario]] in 1992 after Sears pleaded guilty to two counts of sexual assault.<ref name=guru>{{cite news|title=Disgraced doctor is T.O.'s seduction guru|url=http://www.torontosun.com/news/torontoandgta/2008/12/31/7891486.html|accessdate=May 20, 2015|work=Toronto Sun|date=December 30, 2008|quote=\"By 1986, Sears was in the Canadian Armed Forces and while still a third-year medical student was evaluated by a military psychiatrist who suggested there was \"something seriously wrong\" with Sears.\"}}</ref>\n\nSears started the Second Opinion Medical-Legal Consultants Group in 1994, offering \"medical investigative services\" such as medical background checks for the prospective employees of its clients and research for parties to medical malpractice suits. In 2001, it was reported in the ''Toronto Star'' that they had been hired by Canadian Tire and the Toronto Transit Commission.<ref name=torontoist>{{Cite web | url=http://torontoist.com/2017/04/controversial-publisher-ward-news-send-homophobic-hate-mail-councillor-wong-tam/ |title = Did the Controversial Editor of Your Ward News Send Homophobic Hate Mail to Councillor Wong-Tam?|date = 2017-04-19}}</ref>\n\n==Mortgage broker==\nHe has also been involved with the [[mortgage brokerage]] industry with Trillium Mortgages and then Expert Mortgage Company. His application for a mortgage broker's licence was denied by the regulatory body, the [[Financial Services Commission of Ontario]]; however, he has continued to work for Expert Mortgage Company as a \"full-time in-house marketing guru\", describing himself as \"Ontario\u2019s #1 Trainer of Sales Consultants, with Specialization in Mortgage & Real Estate Agents.\"<ref name=torontoist/>\n\n==Pickup artist==\nSears was also known for his activities as a [[pickup artist]] using the pseudonym \"Dimitri the Lover\" selling courses that claimed to train men in how to seduce women.<ref name=torontoist/>\n\n==Politics==\nIn the [[2014 Toronto municipal election|2014 Toronto civic election]], Sears was a [[Toronto City Council|city council]] candidate in Ward 32 and received 797 votes (roughly 3% of the vote).<ref name=\"toronto\">{{cite web|url=http://www1.toronto.ca/City%20Of%20Toronto/City%20Clerks/Elections/Library/Files/Results%20PDFs/2014%20Election/2014-Councillor.pdf|date=31 October 2014|title=2014 Municipal Election Results - Councillor Poll by Poll|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title='Dimitri the Lover' back making headlines|url=http://www.torontosun.com/2015/03/25/dimitri-the-lover-back-making-headlines|accessdate=May 20, 2015|work=Toronto Sun|date=March 25, 2015}}</ref> His campaign included a website with an interactive animation that asked users to choose one of three playable characters, [[Rob Ford]], [[Vladimir Putin]] or [[Adolf Hitler]] to \"spank\" the bare bottom of a cartoon caricature of city councillor [[Mary-Margaret McMahon]], Sears's rival in the election.<ref>{{cite news|title=Toronto city council candidate James Sears promotes online 'spanking' game against female rival|url=http://o.canada.com/news/james-sears-animation-mcmahon-492553|accessdate=May 20, 2015|website=canada.com|agency=Postmedia News|date=June 30, 2014}}</ref>\n\nHe ran in the [[2015 Canadian federal election|2015 federal election]] as an independent candidate (no party affiliation) and placed fifth out of seven candidates, getting 254 votes (less than 0.5% of the vote).<ref name=\"globalnews\">{{cite web|url=http://globalnews.ca/news/2159630/federal-election-2015-beaches-east-york-riding/|title=Federal Election 2015: Beaches-East York riding results - Toronto &#124; Globalnews.ca|publisher=globalnews.ca|accessdate=December 1, 2015}}</ref>\n\nSears was a candidate for the [[Canadians' Choice Party]] in the [[2018 Ontario general election|2018 provincial election]] running against [[Attorney-General of Ontario|Attorney-General]] [[Yasir Naqvi]] in [[Ottawa Centre (provincial electoral district)|Ottawa Centre]]. He placed last out of eight candidates with 92 votes.<ref>https://www.elections.on.ca/content/ngw/en/election-results/ottawa-centre.html</ref>\n\nIn 2018 he registered as a candidate for [[Mayor of Toronto]] in [[2018 Toronto mayoral election|that year's election]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Editor's message |website=Your Ward News |first=James |last=Sears |date=Winter 2018}}</ref> He finished with 680 votes, less than 1% of the total vote.<ref>{{Cite web| url=https://www.toronto.ca/wp-content/uploads/2018/10/97da-2018clerksofficialdeclarationofresults.pdf| title=2018 Clerks Official Declaration of Results| first=Uli| last=Watkiss| date=October 25, 2018| website=toronto.ca| page=1}}</ref>\n\n==''Your Ward News''==\nSears is editor-in-chief of ''Your Ward News'', a quarterly newspaper which promotes the [[Neo-Nazism in Canada#New Constitution Party of Canada|New Constitution Party]], an unregistered [[Neo-Nazism in Canada|neo-Nazi]] political party led by Sears.<ref name=\"ncparty\" /><ref name=ward/> The newspaper used to be printed and distributed as a [[Flyer (pamphlet)|flyer]] in the east [[Toronto]] neighbourhood of [[The Beaches]]. The [[vanity publication]], which claimed to have a circulation of 50,000,<!-- do not change this figure, see talk page --> was criticized for using [[antisemitic]] caricatures and language, described by former [[Canadian Jewish Congress]] Chief Executive Officer [[Bernie Farber]] as \"classic anti-Semitic tropes\" and \"a clear attempt at a hateful representation of Jews\".<ref name=ward>{{cite news|title=Beach residents decry 'offensive' newsletter|url=https://www.thestar.com/news/gta/2015/05/16/beach-residents-decry-offensive-newsletter.html|accessdate=May 20, 2015|work=Toronto Star}}</ref> On June 6, 2016, the [[Government of Canada]] ordered [[Canada Post]] to cease delivery of the paper.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/canada-post-ordered-to-stop-delivering-controversial-your-ward-news-1.3619554 |title=Canada Post ordered to stop delivering controversial Your Ward News |newspaper=CBC News |first=Emmett |last=Shane |date=June 6, 2016 |accessdate=June 7, 2016}}</ref>\n\nThe newspaper continued to be distributed using private delivery services, and was investigated for [[hate crime]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/toronto-police-investigating-controversial-your-ward-news-publication-1.3957831 |title=Toronto police investigating controversial Your Ward News publication |newspaper=CBC News |first=Lauren |last=Pelley |date=January 30, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref> On June 21, 2017, Sears and publisher Leroy St. Germaine were charged under the [[Criminal Code (Canada)|Criminal Code]] with uttering threats against [[Warren Kinsella|Warren and Lisa Kinsella]] in an article by Sears in which he wrote that his supporters may decide to \"bludgeon the Kinsellas to death.\"<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.citynews.ca/2017/06/21/editor-publisher-of-neo-nazi-tabloid-charged-with-uttering-threats/ |title=Editor, publisher of neo-Nazi tabloid charged with uttering threats |website=CityNews |date=June 21, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://toronto.ctvnews.ca/criminal-charges-laid-against-publisher-of-controversial-newspaper-your-ward-news-1.3470015 |title=Criminal charges laid against publisher of controversial newspaper ''Your Ward News'' |website=CTV News |first=Paola |last=Loriggio |publisher=Canadian Press |date=June 21, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2017, Sears and St. Germaine were each charged with two counts of wilful promotion of hatred under the Criminal Code.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.scribd.com/document/398156562/Court-Ruling-Sears-and-St-Germaine|title=Court Ruling - Sears and St. Germaine|website=Scribd|language=en|access-date=2019-01-26}}</ref> They were accused of promoting hatred against women and Jews.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.ctvnews.ca/mobile/canada/2-men-behind-controversial-toronto-publication-face-hate-related-charges-1.3681157 |title=2 men behind controversial Toronto publication face hate-related charges |first=Peter |last=Cameron |publisher=Canadian Press |website=CTV News |date=November 16, 2017 |accessdate=January 4, 2018}}</ref> Both were found guilty on January 24, 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Your Ward News duo found guilty of peddling hate against women and Jews |first=Colin |last=Perkel |newspaper=CBC News |date=January 24, 2019 |url=https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/toronto/your-ward-promoting-hate-1.4990806 |accessdate=January 24, 2019}}</ref> The Crown asked that Sears be given one-year jail sentence and an additional three-years [[probation]] during which Sears would be prohibited from publishing any material.<ref name=\"year\"/> On August 22, 2019, Sears was sentenced to one year's imprisonment, consisting of six months for each charge, served consecutively, the maximum sentence available.<ref name=jail/><ref name=\"year\">{{cite news |last1=Perkel |first1=Colin |title=Editor found guilty of peddling hate says Your Ward News gave 'angry men' a voice |url=https://nationalpost.com/news/canada/crown-seeks-one-year-jail-term-against-editor-convicted-of-promoting-hate |accessdate=April 27, 2019 |work=National Post |agency=Canadian Press |date=April 26, 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Perkel |first1=Colin |title=James Sears fires lawyer; sentencing for Your Ward News delayed |url=https://www.680news.com/2019/05/30/james-sears-fires-lawyer-sentencing-for-your-ward-news-delayed/ |accessdate=June 22, 2019 |work=680 News |agency=Canadian Press |date=May 30, 2019}}</ref> He is currently out on bail, pending appeal.<ref name=bail>{{Cite web | url=https://toronto.citynews.ca/2019/08/29/germaine-your-ward-news-sentence/ | title=Your Ward News publisher sentenced to 12-month house arrest}}</ref> On August 29, 2019, St. Germaine was sentenced to one year of [[house arrest]].<ref name=bail/>\n\n==Electoral record==\n{| cellpadding=\"8\" class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n|+ '''[[2014 Toronto municipal election|2014 Toronto election]], Ward 32'''<ref name=\"2014muni\">{{cite web |title=Toronto Election 2014 Poll By Poll Results: Councillor |url=https://www.toronto.ca/wp-content/uploads/2017/08/9021-election-2014-councillor-poll-by-poll-results.pdf |publisher=Toronto City Clerk's Office |accessdate=June 11, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ddf; width:250px;\"| Candidate\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ddf;\"| Votes\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"background:#ddf;\"| %\n|-\n|[[Mary-Margaret McMahon]]||align=right| 15,762 ||align=right| 60.92\n|-\n|[[Sandra Bussin]] ||align=right| 4,552 ||align=right| 17.59\n|-\n|Brian Graff ||align=right| 1,922 ||align=right| 7.43\n|-\n|'''James Sears''' ||align=right| 797 ||align=right| 3.08\n|-\n|Eric de Boer ||align=right| 677 ||align=right| 2.62\n|-\n|Carmel Suttor ||align=right| 464 ||align=right| 1.79\n|-\n|Alan Burke ||align=right| 404 ||align=right| 1.56\n|-\n|Maria Garcia ||align=right| 402 ||align=right| 1.55\n|-\n|Michael Connor ||align=right| 334 ||align=right| 1.29\n|-\n|Sean Dawson ||align=right| 241 ||align=right| 0.93\n|-\n|Bruce Baker ||align=right| 213 ||align=right| 0.82\n|-\n|Jim Brookman ||align=right| 107 ||align=right| 0.41\n|-\n!Total||align=right| 25,875 ||align=right|  100%\n|}\n{{Canadian federal election, 2015/Beaches\u2014East York}}\n{{Ontario provincial election, 2018/Ottawa Centre}}\n\n==Sources==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Wikiquote}}\n* [http://ncparty.ca Website of the New Constitution Party]\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Sears, James}}\n[[Category:Canadian neo-Nazis]]\n[[Category:Canadian anti-communists]]\n[[Category:Politicians from Toronto]]\n[[Category:Pickup artists]]\n[[Category:Canadian people of Greek descent]]\n[[Category:Canadian newspaper editors]]\n[