Height, Net worth, Birthday, Mother, Boyfriend, Social Media.|date=March 12, 2019|work=edailybuzz.com|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref>\n\nHer mother, Mia, died on 3 June 2013 at the age of 60.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.youtube.com/watch?v=Hj5Y_Mni-eU|title=Amber Mark - Monsoon (Official Video) ft. Mia Mark|work=YouTube|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref> It was her mother who gave Amber her first guitar, which is when she started to teach herself how to play music. In high school, she joined the school choir and an \u201cafter school band program\u201d. She stated in an interview that this was when she realized that being an artist was what she wanted to do.<ref>(2017, August 21) Retrieved November 19, 2019, from https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=R3pNkDnoo5k&t=102s</ref> Her mother was a huge part of her early life and one of her first songs was in dedication to her mother's passing in 2013.<ref>Ciara, H., & Calum, S. (2019, March 12). Amber Mark Wiki, Bio 2019: Age, Height, Net worth, Birthday, Mother, Boyfriend, Social Media. Retrieved from https://edailybuzz.com/2019/03/12/amber-mark-wiki-bio-2019-age-height-net-worth-birthday-mother-boyfriend-social-media/</ref>\n\nAt the age of 4 years old, Amber Mark's mother was able to get concert tickets for [[Michael Jackson]]: The Immortal World Tour. When they arrived they were told that they are not allowed to go to the seating area because Amber was too young at the time. A man at a merchandise table generously gave Amber and her mother \"All Access\" passes as long as they wouldn't go backstage. They ended up seeing the concert from the VIP area and stood next to Boris Becker. Amber remembers crying after the concert was over.\n\n===2016-present:Musical career===\nMark released her debut single \"S P A C E\" to her Soundcloud in 2016.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vice.com/en_us/article/6wq9aq/who-the-hell-is-amber-mark|title=Who the Hell Is Amber Mark?|last=Taylor Bennett|first=Kim|date=April 25, 2016|work=Vice|accessdate=December 4, 2019}}</ref> In 2017 she released her first album \"3:33am\". Mark explains that it was named that because \"Three has been a really common number in my life. My mother was born in 1953, my brother was born in 1983 and I was born in 1993. Then my mum passed away on June 3, at 10:23pm in 2013. Since then, I'd see threes everywhere. When I was writing the EP in New York... and out of the zone, I would check the clock and I always remember it being 3:33am.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.herecomesthesong.com/single-post/2017/07/19/Amber-Mark-a-songwriters-desire-for-more-S-P-A-C-E|title=Amber Mark: a songwriter's desire for more S P A C E|last=Fanthorpe|first=Katie|date=July 19, 2017|work=Here Comes The Song|accessdate=December 4, 2019}}</ref> The album art features a photo taken by her sister, in which Mark is wearing a watch that reads 3:33.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://soundofboston.com/interview-amber-mark/|title=Interview: Amber Mark|last=Bedian|first=Knar|date=2017-10-07|website=Sound of Boston - Boston Music Blog|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref> Each song on the record represents one of the six stages of grief.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://earmilk.com/2017/05/15/amber-mark-shows-prowess-in-life-and-music-on-debut-333am-ep/|title=Amber Mark shows prowess in life and music on debut '3:33am' EP|last=Evans|first=Steph|date=2017-05-15|website=EARMILK|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref> The song \"Monsoon\" includes samples of her mother's voice, which she explained in an interview with [http://www.soundofboston.com Sound of Boston] as \"a video recording of me flying back to New York for the summer while we were living in Berlin. I wanted to make a video for my godmother from my mother. Hence why I\u2019m telling her that they don\u2019t speak German and that she needs to speak English. When she says she loves me that is from a more recent recording she made for me while she was in hospice.\"<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://soundofboston.com/interview-amber-mark/|title=Interview: Amber Mark|last=Bedian|first=Knar|date=2017-10-07|website=Sound of Boston - Boston Music Blog|language=en-US|access-date=2020-01-24}}</ref>\n\nIn 2018 she issued \u201cConexao EP\u201d that included her single \u201cLove Me Right\u201d.<ref>Kellman, Andy. \u201cAmber Mark: Biography, Albums, Streaming Links.\u201d AllMusic, www.allmusic.com/artist/amber-mark-mn0003576734</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of albums\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:24em;\"| Album details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''3:33am''\n|\n* Released: 12 May 2017\n* Label: Virgin EMI\n* Format: [[Music download|digital download]]\n|}\n\n===EPs===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center\"\n|+ List of extended plays\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:9em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:24em;\"| Extended play details\n|-\n! scope=\"row\" | ''Conex\u00e3o''\n|\n* Released: 3 May 2018\n* Label: Virgin EMI\n* Format: [[Music download|digital download]]\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n====As lead artist====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|+ List of singles as lead artist, showing year released and album name\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" | Year\n! scope=\"col\" | Album\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"S P A C E\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/fr/Amber-Mark-Space/release/10359066|title=Amber Mark - Space|work=Discogs|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"3\"| 2016\n| rowspan=\"5\"| ''3:33am''\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Monsoon\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Amber-Mark-Monsoon/release/10359099|title=Amber Mark - Monsoon|work=Discogs|accessdate=December 1, 2019}}</ref><br>{{small| (featuring Mia Mark)}}\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| \"Way Back\"<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.discogs.com/Amber-Mark-Way-Back/release/10359152|title