{"title_page": "Expenditure Management Commission", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2019}}\nThe constitution of '''Expenditure Management Commission''' (EMC) of [[India]] was announced in the Budget Speech by Finance Minister of India [[Arun Jaitley]] in the budget of 2014\u201315.<ref name=thehindu1>{{cite web|last1=Mehra|first1=Puja|title=PM approves constitution of expenditure management panel|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/bimal-jalan-to-head-expenditure-management-commission/article6312580.ece|website=The Hindu|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref> The Commission will be a recommendation body with the primary responsibility of suggesting major expenditure reforms that will enable the government to reduce and manage its [[fiscal deficit]] at more sustainable levels.\n\nThe EMC is a five-member body composed of the former [[Reserve Bank of India]] (RBI) [[Governor]] [[Bimal Jalan]], who has been appointed to head the Commission, former [[Finance Secretary]] Sumit Bose, former Deputy RBI Governor [[Subir Gokarn]] and two other members.<ref name=indiatoday1>{{cite web|title=Bimal Jalan to head Expenditure Management Commission|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/bimal-jalan-to-head-expenditure-management-commission/1/377174.html|website=India Today|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nDespite the legal mandate intended to lower the Fiscal Deficit to 3 per cent within the stipulated time [[Fiscal Responsibility and Budget Management Act, 2003|Fiscal Responsibility and Budgetary Management Act, 2003]], India has witnessed a persistent high [[fiscal deficit]]. Subsidies, public services, underpricing and arbitrary [[natural resource]] allocation are government activities that have led to expenditures greater than revenue.{{Citation needed|reason=Reliable source needed for the whole sentence|date=February 2015}} <ref name=watal1>{{cite journal|last1=Watal|first1=Ratan|title=Constitute_Expenditure_Management_Commission|date=4 September 2014|url=http://finmin.nic.in/the_ministry/dept_expenditure/notification/misc/Constitute_Expenditure_Management_Commission.pdf|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe commission is mandated to evaluate proposals for reducing the three major subsidies (i.e. food, fertilizer and oil).<ref name=livemint1>{{cite web|last1=Mishra|first1=Asit|title=Former RBI head Bimal Jalan to head expenditure management commission|url=http://www.livemint.com/Politics/bME0YV5BaP2laNsVNVQHBO/Former-RBI-head-Bimal-Jalan-to-head-expenditure-management-c.html|website=Livemint|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe commission was to submit an interim report before the presentation of the Budget for 2015\u201316.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/emc-to-submit-interim-report-by-early-january-bimal-jalan-700084|title=EMC to Submit Interim Report by Early January: Bimal Jalan|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref>{{Update after|2015|2|27}} The final report was to be submitted before the 2016-17 budget.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/jalan-panel-on-expenditure-to-submit-report-this-month-1273270|title=Jalan Panel on Expenditure to Submit Report This Month|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/government-examining-report-on-subsidy-rationalisation/articleshow/52145817.cms|title=Government examining report on subsidy rationalisation|date=2016-05-06|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/niti-aayog-to-vet-performance-of-500-autonomous-bodies/articleshow/55129026.cms|title=Niti Aayog to vet performance of 500 autonomous bodies|last=Singh|first=Mahendra K.|date=2016-10-29|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/More-steps-on-the-anvil-for-expenditure-efficiency-Lavasa/articleshow/52832693.cms|title=More steps on the anvil for expenditure efficiency: Lavasa - Times of India|date= 20 June 2016 |newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n[[Category:Government finances in India]]\n[[Category:Modi administration initiatives]]\n[[Category:2014 in Indian economy]]\n[[Category:Expenditure]]\n\n\n{{India-gov-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=May 2019}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=May 2019}}\nThe constitution of '''Expenditure Management Commission''' (EMC) of [[India]] was announced in the Budget Speech by Finance Minister of India [[Arun Jaitley]] in the budget of 2014\u201315.<ref name=thehindu1>{{cite web|last1=Mehra|first1=Puja|title=PM approves constitution of expenditure management panel|url=http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/bimal-jalan-to-head-expenditure-management-commission/article6312580.ece|website=The Hindu|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref> The Commission will be a recommendation body with the primary responsibility of suggesting major expenditure reforms that will enable the government to reduce and manage its [[fiscal deficit]] at more sustainable levels.\n\nThe EMC is a five-member body composed of the former [[Reserve Bank of India]] (RBI) [[Governor]] [[Bimal Jalan]], who has been appointed to head the Commission, former [[Finance Secretary]] Sumit Bose, former Deputy RBI Governor [[Subir Gokarn]] and two other members.<ref name=indiatoday1>{{cite web|title=Bimal Jalan to head Expenditure Management Commission|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/bimal-jalan-to-head-expenditure-management-commission/1/377174.html|website=India Today|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nDespite the legal mandate intended to lower the Fiscal Deficit to 3 per cent within the stipulated time [[Fiscal Responsibility and Budget Management Act, 2003|Fiscal Responsibility and Budgetary Management Act, 2003]], India has witnessed a persistent high [[fiscal deficit]]. Subsidies, public services, underpricing and arbitrary [[natural resource]] allocation are government activities that have led to expenditures greater than revenue.{{Citation needed|reason=Reliable source needed for the whole sentence|date=February 2015}} <ref name=watal1>{{cite journal|last1=Watal|first1=Ratan|title=Constitute_Expenditure_Management_Commission|date=4 September 2014|url=http://finmin.nic.in/the_ministry/dept_expenditure/notification/misc/Constitute_Expenditure_Management_Commission.pdf|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe commission is mandated to evaluate proposals for reducing the three major subsidies (i.e. food, fertilizer and oil).<ref name=livemint1>{{cite web|last1=Mishra|first1=Asit|title=Former RBI head Bimal Jalan to head expenditure management commission|url=http://www.livemint.com/Politics/bME0YV5BaP2laNsVNVQHBO/Former-RBI-head-Bimal-Jalan-to-head-expenditure-management-c.html|website=Livemint|accessdate=27 February 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe commission was to submit an interim report before the presentation of the Budget for 2015-16.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/emc-to-submit-interim-report-by-early-january-bimal-jalan-700084|title=EMC to Submit Interim Report by Early January: Bimal Jalan|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref>{{Update after|2015|2|27}} The final report was to be submitted before the 2016-17 budget.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.ndtv.com/business/jalan-panel-on-expenditure-to-submit-report-this-month-1273270|title=Jalan Panel on Expenditure to Submit Report This Month|website=NDTV.com|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/government-examining-report-on-subsidy-rationalisation/articleshow/52145817.cms|title=Government examining report on subsidy rationalisation|date=2016-05-06|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/economy/policy/niti-aayog-to-vet-performance-of-500-autonomous-bodies/articleshow/55129026.cms|title=Niti Aayog to vet performance of 500 autonomous bodies|last=Singh|first=Mahendra K.|date=2016-10-29|work=The Economic Times|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/delhi/More-steps-on-the-anvil-for-expenditure-efficiency-Lavasa/articleshow/52832693.cms|title=More steps on the anvil for expenditure efficiency: Lavasa - Times of India|date= 20 June 2016 |newspaper=The Times of India|access-date=2019-04-16}}</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n\n[[Category:Government finances in India]]\n[[Category:Modi administration initiatives]]\n[[Category:2014 in Indian economy]]\n[[Category:Expenditure]]\n\n\n{{India-gov-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 2015-16 \u2192 2015\u201316", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Expenditure_Management_Commission"}
{"title_page": "WinZO", "text_new": "{{Infobox company\n| name = WinZO\n| logo = WinZO Logo.png\n| logo_caption = WinZO Trademark\n| image = \n| type = [[Private Company|Private]]\n| industry = Gaming, e-Sports\n| founded = {{Start date and age|2016|10}} in [[New Delhi]], India\n| founders = Paavan Nanda and Saumya Singh Rathore\n| hq_location_city = New Delhi\n| hq_location_country = India\n| area_served = India\n| products = \n| parent = Tictok Skill Games Private Limited\n| website = {{URL|https://www.winzogames.com}}\n}}\n\n'''WinZO''' is a mobile e-Sports gaming platform in India. It is available in 10 regional languages of India.<ref>{{cite web |title=WinZO raises $5 million in Series A Funding from Kalaari and Hike |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/winzo-raises-5-million-in-series-a-funding-from-kalaari-and-hike/articleshow/70329421.cms?from=mdr |website=The Economic Times |date=22 July 2019}}</ref> WinZO Games is operated by TicTok Skill Games Pvt. Ltd.\n\n[[File:WinZO Gold Image.png | thumb | WinZO Home Screen]]\n\n== History ==\n\n'''WinZO''' was co-founded by Paavan Nanda, an [[Indian Institute of Management Calcutta|IIM Calcutta]] alumnus who also co-founded [[ZO Rooms]] & [[Zostel]], and Saumya Singh Rathore who was earlier with [[The Times Group]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Exploring gaming in the vernacular with WinZO |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/technology/exploring-gaming-in-the-vernacular-with-winzo/cid/1725739 |website=www.telegraphindia.com |language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, WinZO Games announced that it has raised $5 Million in Series A funding led by [[Kalaari Capital]] and [[Hike Messenger|Hike]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kalaari, Hike lead $5 mn Series A bet on vernacular gaming platform WinZO |url=https://www.vccircle.com/kalaari-hike-leads-5-mn-series-a-bet-on-vernacular-gaming-platform-winzo |website=VCCircle |date=22 July 2019}}</ref>\n \nWinZO currently has 10 million user base across India.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018We had to build credibility\u2019 - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/people/we-had-to-build-credibility/articleshow/71875885.cms |website=The Times of India}}</ref> WinZO has also set-up a fund of $1.5 Million to support Game Developers in India.<ref>{{cite web |title=Exploring gaming in the vernacular with WinZO |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/technology/exploring-gaming-in-the-vernacular-with-winzo/cid/1725739 |website=www.telegraphindia.com |language=en}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news |title=WinZO raises $5 million in Series A funding from Kalaari and Hike |url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/winzo-raises-5-million-in-series-a-funding-from-kalaari-and-hike/70331336 |publisher=Economic Times Tech}}</ref>\n\nWinZO announced the launch of Game Developers Console in January, 2020 where Gaming Studios and Independent Game Developers across the globe can launch their games on the platform.<ref>{{cite web |title=A game developers console for creators of modern-day games to get better returns |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/a-game-developers-console-for-creators-of-modern-day-games-to-get-better-returns-4794251.html/amp |website=www.moneycontrol.com}}</ref>\n\nIn March, 2020, WinZO announced strategic partnership with Tencent Games India to host [[PlayerUnknown's_Battlegrounds|PUBG Mobile]] Esports in local languages in India. <ref>{{cite web |title=PUBG Mobile, WinZO join hands to bring free tournaments in 10 Indian languages, Rs 1 crore prize money every month |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/tech/pubg-mobile-winzo-join-hands-to-bring-free-tournaments-in-10-indian-languages-rs-1-crore-prize-money-every-month/story-KOwfHxRHtyore6j8tEpb0H.html |website=Hindustan Times |language=en |date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Game Formats ==\n\nWinZO is a platform for users to play skill-games in multiple formats and win cash prizes in return.  \n\n===WinZO Baazi===\n\nWinZO Baazi is a format where users choose a game and can join a group of participants. Users can compete with each other in real time and winner is announced on basis the highest scorer.\n\n===24*7 Tournaments===\n\nIn tournaments, users need to enter tournament only once and can play games multiple times. For the winner announcements, only the best score of each user is counted.\n\n===1-vs-1 Matches===\n\nIn this format, two players play their selected games against each other. Player, who scores the maximum between two players, is announced winner at the end of game.\n\n===Fantasy Sports===\n\nIn Fantasy Sports, WinZO provides a platform for its users to create a virtual team of upcoming sports events. Points are allocated to the virtual teams based on the real life performance of the players. At the end of the event, users are rewarded basis the ranking of their teams.\n\n==Awards==\n\n2019: Startup of the year - Technology by [[Entrepreneur India]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.entrepreneurindia.com/awards_winner.php|title=AWARD WINNERS|last=|first=|date=|website=www.entrepreneurindia.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n2020: Inc42 Startup Watchlist: Indian Media & Entertainment Startups To Watch Out For In 2020. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://inc42.com/features/startup-watchlist-indian-media-entertainment-startups-to-watch-out-for-in-2020/|title=Startup Watchlist: Indian Media & Entertainment Startups To Watch Out For In 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=www.inc42.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n2020: SutraHR - \"100\" Top Startups in India. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://sutrahr.com/top-startups-india-2020-best-list|title=THE FOLLOWING ARE THE \"100\" TOP STARTUPS IN INDIA 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=www.sutrahr.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n2020: [[Businessworld]] Techtors 2020. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.businessworld.in/article/Over-15-Tech-Disrupters-Awarded-At-BW-TechTors-2020/23-01-2020-182632/|title=Over 15 Tech Disrupters Awarded At BW TechTors 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=www.businessworld.in|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n[[Category:Esports websites]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox company\n| name = WinZO\n| logo = WinZO Logo.png\n| logo_caption = WinZO Trademark\n| image = \n| type = [[Private Company|Private]]\n| industry = Gaming, e-Sports\n| founded = October, 2016\n| founded = {{Start date and age|2016|10}} in [[New Delhi]], India\n| founders = Paavan Nanda and Saumya Singh Rathore\n| hq_location_city = New Delhi\n| hq_location_country = India\n| area_served = India\n| products = \n| parent = Tictok Skill Games Private Limited\n| website = {{URL|https://www.winzogames.com}}\n}}\n\n'''WinZO''' is a mobile e-Sports gaming platform in India. It is available in 10 regional languages of India.<ref>{{cite web |title=WinZO raises $5 million in Series A Funding from Kalaari and Hike |url=https://economictimes.indiatimes.com/small-biz/startups/newsbuzz/winzo-raises-5-million-in-series-a-funding-from-kalaari-and-hike/articleshow/70329421.cms?from=mdr |website=The Economic Times |date=22 July 2019}}</ref> WinZO Games is operated by TicTok Skill Games Pvt. Ltd.\n\n[[File:WinZO Gold Image.png | thumb | WinZO Home Screen]]\n\n== History ==\n\n'''WinZO''' was co-founded by Paavan Nanda, an [[Indian Institute of Management Calcutta|IIM Calcutta]] alumnus who also co-founded [[ZO Rooms]] & [[Zostel]], and Saumya Singh Rathore who was earlier with [[The Times Group]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Exploring gaming in the vernacular with WinZO |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/technology/exploring-gaming-in-the-vernacular-with-winzo/cid/1725739 |website=www.telegraphindia.com |language=en}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2019, WinZO Games announced that it has raised $5 Million in Series A funding led by [[Kalaari Capital]] and [[Hike Messenger|Hike]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kalaari, Hike lead $5 mn Series A bet on vernacular gaming platform WinZO |url=https://www.vccircle.com/kalaari-hike-leads-5-mn-series-a-bet-on-vernacular-gaming-platform-winzo |website=VCCircle |date=22 July 2019}}</ref>\n \nWinZO currently has 10 million user base across India.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u2018We had to build credibility\u2019 - Times of India |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/people/we-had-to-build-credibility/articleshow/71875885.cms |website=The Times of India}}</ref> WinZO has also set-up a fund of $1.5 Million to support Game Developers in India.<ref>{{cite web |title=Exploring gaming in the vernacular with WinZO |url=https://www.telegraphindia.com/technology/exploring-gaming-in-the-vernacular-with-winzo/cid/1725739 |website=www.telegraphindia.com |language=en}}</ref>\n<ref>{{cite news |title=WinZO raises $5 million in Series A funding from Kalaari and Hike |url=https://tech.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/startups/winzo-raises-5-million-in-series-a-funding-from-kalaari-and-hike/70331336 |publisher=Economic Times Tech}}</ref>\n\nWinZO announced the launch of Game Developers Console in January, 2020 where Gaming Studios and Independent Game Developers across the globe can launch their games on the platform.<ref>{{cite web |title=A game developers console for creators of modern-day games to get better returns |url=https://www.moneycontrol.com/news/trends/entertainment/a-game-developers-console-for-creators-of-modern-day-games-to-get-better-returns-4794251.html/amp |website=www.moneycontrol.com}}</ref>\n\nIn March, 2020, WinZO announced strategic partnership with Tencent Games India to host [[PlayerUnknown's_Battlegrounds|PUBG Mobile]] Esports in local languages in India. <ref>{{cite web |title=PUBG Mobile, WinZO join hands to bring free tournaments in 10 Indian languages, Rs 1 crore prize money every month |url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/tech/pubg-mobile-winzo-join-hands-to-bring-free-tournaments-in-10-indian-languages-rs-1-crore-prize-money-every-month/story-KOwfHxRHtyore6j8tEpb0H.html |website=Hindustan Times |language=en |date=24 March 2020}}</ref>\n\n== Game Formats ==\n\nWinZO is a platform for users to play skill-games in multiple formats and win cash prizes in return.  \n\n===WinZO Baazi===\n\nWinZO Baazi is a format where users choose a game and can join a group of participants. Users can compete with each other in real time and winner is announced on basis the highest scorer.\n\n===24*7 Tournaments===\n\nIn tournaments, users need to enter tournament only once and can play games multiple times. For the winner announcements, only the best score of each user is counted.\n\n===1-vs-1 Matches===\n\nIn this format, two players play their selected games against each other. Player, who scores the maximum between two players, is announced winner at the end of game.\n\n===Fantasy Sports===\n\nIn Fantasy Sports, WinZO provides a platform for its users to create a virtual team of upcoming sports events. Points are allocated to the virtual teams based on the real life performance of the players. At the end of the event, users are rewarded basis the ranking of their teams.\n\n==Awards==\n\n2019: Startup of the year - Technology by [[Entrepreneur India]] <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.entrepreneurindia.com/awards_winner.php|title=AWARD WINNERS|last=|first=|date=|website=www.entrepreneurindia.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n2020: Inc42 Startup Watchlist: Indian Media & Entertainment Startups To Watch Out For In 2020. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://inc42.com/features/startup-watchlist-indian-media-entertainment-startups-to-watch-out-for-in-2020/|title=Startup Watchlist: Indian Media & Entertainment Startups To Watch Out For In 2020|last=|first=|date=|website=www.inc42.com|language=en|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=}}</ref>\n\n2020: SutraHR - \"100\" Top Startups in India. <ref>{{cite web|ur