14]]: Chennur(Assembly constituency)}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party=Telangana Rashtra Samithi|candidate=[[Nallala Odelu]]|votes=64,867|percentage=51.44%|change=}}\n{{Election box candidate with party link|party=Indian National Congress|candidate=Gaddam Vinod|votes=38,703|percentage=30.69%|change=}}\n\n{{Election box majority|votes=26,164|percentage=|change=}}\n{{Election box turnout|votes=1,26,102|percentage=74.07%|change=}}\n{{Election box hold with party link\n| winner =Telangana Rashtra Samithi \n|loser        =Indian National Congress\n| swing  = \n}}\n{{Election box end}}\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of constituencies of Telangana Legislative Assembly]]\n\n==External links==\n* [https://web.archive.org/web/20150215232004/http://www.chennur.in/ Chennur Constituency Website]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}2. https://www.ndtv.com/elections/Telangana/chennur-MLA-results<nowiki/>{{Assembly constituencies of Telangana}}\n\n{{coord missing|Telangana}}\n\n[[Category:Assembly constituencies of Telangana]]\n[[Category:Mancherial district]]\n\n\n{{India-gov-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2019}}\n{{short description|Constituency of the Telangana legislative assembly in India}}\n{{Infobox Vidhan Sabha constituency\n| name               = Chennur\n| map                =\n| state              = [[Telangana]]\n| union_territory    = \n| district           = [[mancherial district|Mancherial]]\n| electorate         = 1,49,679\n| year               = 1952-1957(Chennur-Sirpur Kagaznagar)1957-1962(Chennur-Laxetipet) 1962(Chennur Constituency)  \n| reserved           = SC\n| mla                = [[Balka Suman]]  \n| party              = [[Telangana Rashtra Samithi]]\n}}\n'''Chennur Assembly Constituency''' is a constituency of  [[List of constituencies of Telangana Legislative Assembly|Telangana Legislative Assembly]], India.Initially it was two member Constituency till 1962 ,later it was Created as Single Member Constituency in the year 1962    It is one of three constituencies in [[Mancherial district]]. Chennur is located in south of the [[Mancherial district]]. It comes under [[Peddapally (Lok Sabha constituency)|Peddapally Lok Sabha constituency]].\n\n[[Balka Suman]] of [[Telangana Rashtra Samithi]] is representing the constituency for the first time.\n\n==Mandals==\nThe Assembly Constituency presently comprises the following Mandals:\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n|-\n! S.No. !! Mandal\n|-\n| 1|| Chennur\n|-\n| 2|| Mandamarri\n|-\n| 3|| Kotapalli\n|-\n| 4|| Jaipur\n|-\n| 5|| Bheemaram\n|}\n\n== Members of Legislative Assebmbly ==\nMembers of Legislative Assembly who represented Chennur<ref>https://eci.nic.in/eci_main/electionanalysis/AE/S01/partycomp263.htm</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year !! Winner !! Party !! Runner-up !! Party\n|-\n| 1957-62 ||[[G. Venkatswamy]]|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC|| n/a|| IND\n|-\n| 1978 ||C. Narayana|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC|| n/a|| IND\n|-\n| 1983|| S. Sanjiva Rao|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC|| n/a|| IND\n|-\n| 1985|| [[Boda Janardhan]]\t|| bgcolor=\"#FFFF31\" |TDP || G.Venkat Swamy|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n|-\n| 1989|| [[Boda Janardhan]]\t|| bgcolor=\"#FFFF31\" |TDP|| G.Vinod|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n|-\n| 1994|| [[Boda Janardhan]]\t|| bgcolor=\"#FFFF31\" |TDP|| G.Vinod\t|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n|-\n| 1999|| [[Boda Janardhan]]|| bgcolor=\"#FFFF31\" |TDP|| G.Vinod\t|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n|-\n| 2004|| G. Vinod\t|| bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC||  [[Boda Janardhan]]\t|| bgcolor=\"#FFFF31\" |TDP\n|-\n| 2009|| [[Nallala Odelu]]\t||bgcolor=\"#ff89ce\" | TRS || G. VINOD || bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n|-\n| 2010|| [[Nallala Odelu]] (By Polls) ||bgcolor=\"#ff89ce\" | TRS || G.Vinod || bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n|-\n| 2014|| [[Nallala Odelu]]\t||bgcolor=\"#ff89ce\" | TRS || G.Vinod || bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n|-\n| 2018|| [[Balka Suman]]\t||bgcolor=\"#ff89ce\" | TRS || Venkatesh Netha Borlakunta || bgcolor=\"#00FFFF\" | INC\n\n|}\n\n==Election resu